description:
Claude Bolling composed this suite for jazz combo (piano, drums, and stand-up bass) and classical trumpet especially for the legendary trumpet Maurice Andre. It is in six movements, each movement featuring a different style and instrument (trumpet in c, piccolo trumpet in b-flat, flugelhorn, cornet in b-flat, and classical trumpet in e-flat). It is a true virtuosic masterpiece and Maurice Andre performs it with the compose with his usual excellence.
